This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a method for learning temporal embeddings of video frames for complex video analysis. It also mentions tasks such as retrieval, classification, and temporal order recovery, which are commonly associated with computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) sub-category. 

The use of embeddings and data augmentation techniques could also place this paper in the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper involves the analysis of large quantities of unlabeled video data, which could suggest that it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a scheme for incorporating temporal context, which could place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as temporal context is also important in language processing tasks.
